{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/go-serverless-with-firebase-5348dedb70e9", "time": 1682993234.8527942, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/go-serverless-with-firebase-5348dedb70e9/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Go Serverless with Firebase. All about serverless what, why and how? | by Anuradha Wickramarachchi | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Go Serverless with Firebase", "description": "In simple terms, Serverless architecture is a programming paradigm that focusses on coding functions for web-endpoints directly rather than going through the whole process of setting up a server\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://aws.amazon.com/lambda/", "anchor_text": "AWS Lambda", "paragraph_index": 1}, {"url": "https://aws.amazon.com/dynamodb/?nc2=h_m1", "anchor_text": "Amazon Dynamo", "paragraph_index": 1}, {"url": "https://www.mongodb.com/cloud/atlas", "anchor_text": "MongoDB Atlas", "paragraph_index": 1}], "all_paragraphs": ["In simple terms, Serverless architecture is a programming paradigm that focusses on coding functions for web-endpoints directly rather than going through the whole process of setting up a server, routing requests, defining REST resources and then creating methods for GET, POST and PUT. Still confused? Well in programmers\u2019 terminology we just need to code the method body, everything else is provided off the shelf from the service provider.", "The most common serverless service provider is Amazon, with their AWS Lambda service. Which is a highly scalable solution which is extensively used in enterprise level application. Most of those service are used either with Amazon Dynamo or MongoDB Atlas. Starting off with AWS and building an application is quite cumbersome, though it has so many features and cool integrations. So let\u2019s do the same with Firebase!! :)", "Other than the simplicity, serverless architecture has few other advantages. Since you are only programming the logic of a web service, scalability will no longer be an issue. You will only be charged for the execution times, which means no amount will be charged for unused functions. Firebase has made the authentication way easier with their authentication platform. After all, this has some down side as well. You might not be aware of the underlying hardware so in some cases, you will have to adhere to the standard hardware apis they provide. But for storage Google provides Google storage and AWS provide S3 buckets for this purpose.", "I think this is the most interesting thing. Let\u2019s make a simple application using a firebase cloud function, thats the name they call for serverless architecture.", "Now that you have created an app, you will have some NPM packages to install.", "You will be asked to login by opening the browser. Login accordingly. Now use the following command to start the project.", "Select Cloud Functions and press Enter, then select the created project and press Enter. In the same project folder create a folder named functions, go to that and initiate a Node project as follows.", "Now create an index.js file and create functions assuming its a normal Node JS server side code. An example code is as follows.", "If you are familiar with Node JS, its clear that this function returns the query parameters and body parameters back to the user.", "You can now deploy the application. For that we can use the following command.", "Once the deployment ends, you will be given with the function URL. You can either paste it on browser and send a GET request, or POST request via a REST API test tool.", "That was a lot of work? Well once you get these steps sorted you can focus on coding just the functions, The above code was the only code I needed to code by my self ;-). You can easily connect with Firebase Database, Storage or Authentication to make a complete application. Also, you can do a lot with the free quota.", "I hope you enjoyed reading this. Fire-up your next project, Cheers!!", "Your home for data science.